    <eval phase="PreLevel" priority="5000"><![CDATA[     if (container.parent.field[gIsEquip].value <> 0) then
        ~ Add a +5 enh bonus to our Climb and Esc Artist skill
        #enhancementbonus[hero.child[kClimb], 4]
        #enhancementbonus[hero.child[kEscape], 4]
        endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="ipSpdrBoun" name="Spider Bound" description="{b}Price:{/b} +2,500 gp (buckler), +5,000 gp (light shield), +10,000 gp (heavy shield), +15,000 gp (tower shield)\n{b}Property:{/b} Shield\n{b}Caster Level:{/b} 12th\n{b}Aura:{/b} Strong; (DC 21) conjuration\n{b}Activation:{/b} Standard Action (command)\n\n{i}This shield resembles a large spider. The small rubies used for its eyes burn with a hellish light.{/i}\n\nOnce per day, you can speak a command word to cause your shield to transform into a fi endish spider. The spider&#146;s size depends on the type of shield, as shown on the following table.\n\n{b}                            Fiendish Monstrous \nShield                Spider Size{/b}\nBuckler             Small\nLight shield      Medium\nHeavy shield    Large\nTower shield    Huge\n\nThe spider follows your mental commands.\nIt remains for 10 rounds or until reduced to 0 hit points, at which point it instantly reverts back to a shield. While the spider is activated, you lose your shield bonus to AC.\n\n{i}Prerequisite:{/i}  Craft Magic Arms and Armor, {i}summon monster I{/i} (buckler), {i}summon monster II{/i} (light shield), {i}summon monster IV[/i} (heavy shield), {i}summon monster VI{/i} (tower shield), drow.\n{i}Cost to Create:{/i} 1,250 gp, 100 XP, 3 days (buckler); 2,500 gp, 200 XP, 5 days (light shield); 5,000 gp, 400 XP, 10 days (heavy shield); 7,500 gp, 600 XP, 15 days (tower shield).\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Drow of the Underdark{/i} 3.5 Edition" compset="ItemPower" summary="Can transform you shield into a spider, based on size.">
