  <thing id="ioBeltReFo" name="Belt of the Reinforced Form" description="{b}Price:{/b} 5,400 gp (10th)\n{b}Property:{/b} Waist\n{b}Caster Level:{/b} 7th\n{b}Aura:{/b} Moderate; (DC 18) transmutation\n{b}Activation:{/b} &#151;\n{b}Weight:{/b} 1 lb.\n\n{i}This wide belt is made of orange scaly leather. Despite its appearance, it is soft and pliable. The adamantine buckle is set with a strange teardrop gemstone that changes color in the light.{/i}\n\nWhile you wear a {i}belt of the reinforced form{/i}, whenever you are the target of a transmutation spell or spell-like effect, or some other transformative effect such as an aboleth&#146;s slime or a basilisk&#146;s petrifying gaze, you gain a +4 bonus on your saving throw.\nIn addition, once per day, when casting a transmutation spell with a casting time of 1 standard action on yourself, you can cast that spell as a swift action \ninstead.\n\n{i}Prerequisite:{/i}  Craft Wondrous Item, {i}alter self{/i}, {i}haste{/i}.\n{i}Cost to Create:{/i} 2,700 gp, 216 XP, 6 days.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Drow of the Underdark{/i} 3.5 Edition" compset="Wondrous" summary="+4 boon vs transf attacks.  1/day, cast transf. spls as swift.">
