  <thing id="irResolve" name="Ring of Resolve" description="{b}Price:{/b} 5,500 gp (10th)\n{b}Property:{/b} Ring\n{b}Caster Level:{/b} 13th\n{b}Aura:{/b} Strong; (DC 21)\n{b}Activation:{/b}  &#151; and immediate (command)\n{b}Weight:{/b} &#151;\n\n{i}Eight small diamonds encrust this adamantine ring.{/i}\n\nA {i}ring of resolve{/i} grants you a +4 morale bonus on Will saves made against spells and spell-like effects with the fear descriptor. This is a continuous effect and requires no activation.\nOnce per day, as an immediate action you can turn back a fear spell or spelllike effect against the original caster as long as that effect had you as the target.\nFor all aspects of the spell, the effect functions as if the original caster had selected itself as the target.\n\n{i}Prerequisite:{/i} Forge Ring, {i}spell turning{/i}.\n{i}Cost to Create:{/i} 2,750 gp, 220 XP, 6 days.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Drow of the Underdark{/i} 3.5 Edition" compset="Ring" summary="+4 Morale vs fear.  1/day, return a targeted fear back on its caster.">
