  <thing id="irExcrucia" name="Excruciating Ring" description="{b}Price:{/b} 8,000 gp (11th)\n{b}Property:{/b} Ring\n{b}Caster Level:{/b} 5th\n{b}Aura:{/b} Faint; (DC 17) necromancy\n{b}Activation:{/b} Immediate (command)\n{b}Weight:{/b} &#151;\n\n{i}This bone ring is set with a marble-sized stone of white onyx.{/i}\n\nAn {i}excruciating ring{/i} punishes those who would touch you. Five times per day as an immediate action, when struck by a melee attack, you can send a lance of pain through your opponent, dealing 2d6 points of nonlethal damage.\n\n{i}Prerequisite:{/i} Forge Ring, {i}death armor{/i} (SC).\n{i}Cost to Create:{/i} 4,000 gp, 160 XP, 8 days.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Drow of the Underdark{/i} 3.5 Edition" compset="Ring" summary="5/day (on command), 2d6 nonlethal damage to those who attack you.">
