  <thing id="ioSpiderBo" name="Spider Box" description="{b}Price:{/b} 3,200 gp (8th)\n{b}Property:{/b} &#151; \n{b}Caster Level:{/b} 7th\n{b}Aura:{/b} Moderate; (DC 18) conjuration\n{b}Activation:{/b} &#151; and tandard\n{b}Weight:{/b} 2 lbs\n\n{i}This pale white stone box is carved with bas-reliefs depicting spiders of all shapes and sizes. Some wriggling thing within the container causes it to shake violently.{/i}\n\nWhen a {i}spider box{/i} is in your possession, you gain a +4 resistance bonus on saving throws against spiderkind poison.\nAlso, when you place a {i}spider box{/i} on any level surface and speak the command word, the box unfolds and releases a swarm of spiders (MM 239).\nThe creatures respond to your silent commands, attacking where you direct them for a maximum of 7 rounds. Commanding the creatures to change targets is a move action.\nA {i}spider box{/i} can be used twice per day.\nOnly one swarm can be in existence at a time. If the swarm is destroyed or the duration ends, the box reassembles, awaiting your next command to open it.\n\n{i}Prerequisite:{/i} Craft Wondrous Item, {i}summon swarm{/i}.\n{i}Cost to Create:{/i} 1,600 gp, 128 XP, 4 days.\n\n{b}Source:{/b} {i}Drow of the Underdark{/i} 3.5 Edition" compset="Wondrous" summary="+4 resist to spiderkind poisons. 2/day, summon swarm of spiders.">
